tweet:
Susceptible host

Some people are more susceptible than others to certain infectious agents. Age, cold weather and underlying health conditions can make an individual more at risk of infection. 

By identifying and addressing underlying risks the chain of infection can be broken. https://t.co/BXFtxjTnoA
tweet_en:
Susceptible host

Some people are more susceptible than others to certain infectious agents. Age, cold weather and underlying health conditions can make an individual more at risk of infection. 

By identifying and addressing underlying risks the chain of infection can be broken. https://t.co/BXFtxjTnoA

tweet:
Portal of Entry

To prevent the infectious agent entering a host & multiplying, health professionals can take the following steps to break the chain of infection:

▶️ensure staff/patients maintain good personal hygiene 
▶️follow guidance on wound care & catheter insertion & care https://t.co/5WsC3IeVNL
tweet_en:
Portal of Entry

To prevent the infectious agent entering a host & multiplying, health professionals can take the following steps to break the chain of infection:

▶️ensure staff/patients maintain good personal hygiene 
▶️follow guidance on wound care & catheter insertion & care https://t.co/5WsC3IeVNL

tweet:
The Mode of Transmission

The following actions can help to break the chain at the point where an agent is transmitted to the site of infection:
▶️maintain hand hygiene
▶️keep your immediate environment clean
▶️handle food safely
▶️appropriate use of PPE https://t.co/JqYFpa8SqW
tweet_en:
The Mode of Transmission

The following actions can help to break the chain at the point where an agent is transmitted to the site of infection:
▶️maintain hand hygiene
▶️keep your immediate environment clean
▶️handle food safely
▶️appropriate use of PPE https://t.co/JqYFpa8SqW

tweet:
Portal of Exit

This is often through sneezing, coughing, and also through poo, vomit, urine, blood and other body fluids.

To break the chain:
▶️health professionals should wear & dispose of PPE safely
▶️everyone should maintain good hand hygiene https://t.co/nOuXz0hBNP
tweet_en:

tweet:
The Reservoir

The place where the microorganism normally lives, grows & multiplies.

Taking antibiotics contributes to the colonisation of resistant organisms in the gut. 

Help break the chain of infection through antimicrobial stewardship & education: https://t.co/vj14Z7Qfy8
tweet_en:
The Reservoir

The place where the microorganism normally lives, grows & multiplies.

Taking antibiotics contributes to the colonisation of resistant organisms in the gut. 

Help break the chain of infection through antimicrobial stewardship & education: https://t.co/vj14Z7Qfy8

tweet:
The Agent [Part III]

Prevention is preferable to the antibiotic cure. The more we use antibiotics, the less effective they become: https://t.co/HIhMWX9xjL

The resistant organisms – the agents – live in the gut and the gut is the human reservoir, the place where agents live.
tweet_en:
The Agent [Part III]

Prevention is preferable to the antibiotic cure. The more we use antibiotics, the less effective they become: https://t.co/HIhMWX9xjL

The resistant organisms – the agents – live in the gut and the gut is the human reservoir, the place where agents live.

tweet:
The Agent [Part II]

Preventing infections in the first place means that health professionals do not need to prescribe antibiotics. This is important because infectious agents are becoming increasingly resistant to antibiotics, this is known as Antimicrobial Resistance (#AMR). https://t.co/6mFEtOjaIy
tweet_en:
The Agent [Part II]

Preventing infections in the first place means that health professionals do not need to prescribe antibiotics. This is important because infectious agents are becoming increasingly resistant to antibiotics, this is known as Antimicrobial Resistance (#AMR). https://t.co/6mFEtOjaIy

tweet:
The Agent [Part I]

Infectious agents include viruses (e.g. COVID-19 or flu) and bacteria, such as MRSA. Understanding the different agents and the interventions that stop them from spreading helps us to break the chain. https://t.co/xnISnRwgPF
tweet_en:

tweet: The JCVI, which advises government on vaccine use and prioritisation, regularly reviews data and evidence on #vaccine efficacy and effectiveness.
tweet_en: The JCVI, which advises government on vaccine use and prioritisation, regularly reviews data and evidence on #vaccine efficacy and effectiveness.

tweet: Evidence shows that the #vaccine is working in older people and among healthcare workers and this will help prevent the virus spreading among clinically vulnerable groups.
tweet_en: Evidence shows that the #vaccine is working in older people and among healthcare workers and this will help prevent the virus spreading among clinically vulnerable groups.

tweet: We know that people whose immune systems are compromised may not respond as well to the #vaccine, which is why it’s vital that these groups continue to shield in line with the guidance.
tweet_en: We know that people whose immune systems are compromised may not respond as well to the #vaccine, which is why it’s vital that these groups continue to shield in line with the guidance.

tweet: It’s important to remember that the study looks at people’s immune responses to the #Pfizer #COVID19 #vaccine but did not measure actual protection. It involves very small numbers of people and has not yet been peer reviewed.
tweet_en: It’s important to remember that the study looks at people’s immune responses to the #Pfizer #COVID19 #vaccine but did not measure actual protection. It involves very small numbers of people and has not yet been peer reviewed.

tweet: We know some people may be concerned at reading about the findings of this study, which looks at the immune response to the first dose of the #Pfizer #COVID19 #vaccine in #cancer patients: https://t.co/3X2wUVYU96
